    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "1.1 Recruitment of consultant  1.2 Preparation of Inception Report1.3 Prepare and finalize preparedness documents (contingency plan/surveillance plan/laboratory protocol) for Glanders1.4 Assess the DLS animal disease reporting system to identify gaps in national animal disease reporting system1.5 Capacity of government/non-government/private animal and public health professionals improved in Glanders recognition and reporting1.6 Conduct awareness training to brick kilns owners/workers and workers involved with cart pulling where horses/mules are used on Glanders recognition and preventive measures1.7 Development of communication materials (e.g. brochure, flyer, posters) on Glanders and neglected zoonotic diseases in local language1.8. Development of the Project concept note on Glanders disease management and other horse diseases2.1 Strengthen/ establish diagnostic capacity at CVL and other laboratories for Glanders2.2. Mapping of equine (horse species) populations and risk assessment of Glanders transmission at animal-human interface in Nepal2.3 Conduct surveillance/ screening of horse/mule population at brick kilns and other risk areas in Nepal for Glanders as per the surveillance plan developed by DLS.2.4 Conduct a study to estimate financial impact due to Glanders in Nepal2.5 Capacity building of laboratory staff for Glanders diagnosis"
      },
      "ne": null
    },
